{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "615454d751cc1e09b41d2a1e", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": null, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": null, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "NTAS1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76e4c52ffa3c944600e1"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eb9a"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [{"title": "NTA Abhyas Paper", "value": "26", "isVisible": true}], "previousYearPapers": [], "question": {"text": "A parallel plate capacitor of capacitance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>&nbsp;is connected to a battery and is charged to a potential difference <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math></em>. Another capacitor of capacitance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>&nbsp;is similarly charged to a potential difference <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>. The charging battery is now disconnected and the capacitors are connected in parallel to each other in such a way that the positive terminal of one is connected to the negative terminal of the other. The final energy of the configuration is", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "qoKo6", "text": "zero", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "EAViS", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>25</mn><mn>6</mn></mfrac><msup><mtext>CV</mtext><mn>2</mn></msup></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "HXkKA", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mtext>CV</mtext><mn>2</mn></msup></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "fc03p", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mtext>CV</mtext><mn>2</mn></msup></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "The diagramatic representation of given problem is shown in the figure.<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/nta_abhyas/neet/images/EM0001668.png\" style=\"width: 422px; height: 221px;\" /><br />The net charge shared between the two capacitors is,<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>Q</mtext><mo>'</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><msub><mtext>Q</mtext><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mtext>Q</mtext><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mtext>CV</mtext><mo>-</mo><mtext>CV</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mtext>CV&#160;</mtext></math><br /><br />The two capacitors will have the same potential, say <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>V</mtext><mo>'</mo></msup></math>.<br />The net capacitance of the parallel combination of the two capacitors will be,<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>C</mtext><mo>'</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><msub><mtext>C</mtext><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mtext>C</mtext><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mtext>C</mtext><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mtext>C</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mtext>C</mtext></math><br /><br />The potential difference across the capacitors will be,<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>V</mtext><mo>'</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msup><mtext>Q</mtext><mo>'</mo></msup><msup><mtext>C</mtext><mo>'</mo></msup></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mtext>CV</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mtext>C</mtext></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mtext>V&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</mtext></math><br /><br />The electrostatic energy of the capacitors will be,<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>U</mtext><mo>'</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mtext>C</mtext><mo>'</mo></msup><msup><mtext>V</mtext><msup><mo>'</mo><mn>2</mn></msup></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mtext>C</mtext></mrow></mfenced><msup><mtext>V</mtext><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mtext>CV</mtext><mn>2</mn></msup><mspace/></math><br />&nbsp;</p><style type=\"text/css\"><!--\t\t@page { margin: 2cm }\t\tP { margin-bottom: 0.21cm }\t--></style>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["616024041a305c0e66419287", "61602405c04b6efc2d30aed2", "61964c87b2e3ece4a3ae08f5", "61c089968f11857e2cc22ac4", "61964c88aedbe61edbf4a8ad", "6160240548aa12a5f67c1a13", "61bb8218a1451a3af02543bc", "61e7bd7581a69b0b3a599b78", "61602402632932165bf0ef64", "61602407c6302cf0196ff8b1", "629109ecd51d11c3d30d1b00", "629621228b45dfe178855e12", "629f390b647d372f60ea38d1", "629f3a90c1d078c63b9fb649", "64eb06c23118f713ecfef091", "66d58538a75f05ee8564f554", "67921d6a1d5b5072da5e9ada", "67fdff48378e1624ea7b699b", "6809202d3a10446a207fdefc"], "cpyqbExams": ["616059d70283de43c87e3e24", "616059730283de43c87